fields.content:
Finally we are in the car on our way to the Melbourne Home & Giving Fair. The tarp over the back of the trailer fortunately hasn’t blown off this year (yet). This is months of preparation finding fabric, finishing designs, and printing samples (the last one wasn’t dry when we set off in the car).

Our first trade show was in 1999 with three designs and four samples. It’s the anticipation, the people and the atmosphere that we look forward to at the trade fairs. Melbourne always draws a great crowd. Now all I need to do is put up the stand and write some orders.

As I type, our website is about to make its grand entrance to the public. It will be Eastbourne Art’s first online shop. I keep thinking I need to be somewhere. But we are assured by Claire (my daughter), that the shop will run without us.

The Melbourne Home & Giving Fair is on from 7th - 11th August at the Melbourne Exhibition Centre & Melbourne Showgrounds. Come and visit us at stand S46.
fields.title: Home & Giving Fair - Melbourne

fields.content:
Welcome to our much anticipated online shop.

Yes it took us a few years to get here, but we are finally here. And what a website we have. With thanks to Claire and Craig and the team at 1MD. Finally the ‘our website will launch in May 2009’ page is coming down!

The launch of this website comes after many months of gathering content, pouring over product spreadsheets, photographing stock,  testing and more testing, making sure the site was ‘us’, and of course getting ready to take the business online.

For those who have subscribed to our mailing list, we will be sending you a long awaited email in the coming weeks with our new range, including our Christmas goodies.

We’d love to hear your feedback on the website. Welcome :)
fields.title: Our website goes live.....finally!

fields.content:
We are back from Melbourne, having had a great reception to our new range. Birds and trees, spots and stripes hit the mark.

The trade fair this year had a buzz, lots of new faces. The trend is still with the natural colours & vintage-french inspired homewares. Now its back to work....collating, making & producing for all the orders taken.

Our new range will be available online in the coming week. We have sent the products off to get photographed. Next year we hope to be ahead and have the products ready to view at trade fair time. It was very ambitious to launch a website and get to the trade fair at the same time.

I have posted some photos of our stand in Melbourne. We spent some time thinking about how the stand would come together, and my painted tree idea looked great and it was fun to do. Amazingly it didn't launch itself off the back of the trailer, or attack any of the cars behind it!!
fields.title: Back home, back to work....

fields.content:
My first blog post, or shall I say, a few words from amongst the vines. Although at this time of year it’s more like amongst the twigs, as everything is dormant. Just as well, as I haven’t had any time for our now-six year old grapes.

It’s only three or four weeks until the vines start to bud, an exciting time in the cycle of a vineyard. Warmer days mean the buds form, and then my favourite time; bud-burst.

Ruby and Indi (our ever faithful Labradors) have been busy keeping an eye on the farm renovations. That is, when they aren’t off adventuring in the bush land, or being fed by our friendly neighbours. The works are due to finish come Spring, so long as the weather sticks to the plan & the windows and doors arrive (if they ever do!). As the project draws closer to the finish line its exciting to drive up the driveway on a work day and see what’s new.

Eastbourne Art operates out of a purpose built shed on the property. A long way from a few shelves in the family room. Many of my long-standing clients will remember browsing the current range over the billiard table in amongst kids (four of them), dogs and family life.

Eastbourne Art is a collection inspired by my everyday life. There has always been a skew towards garden & outdoors, as it’s where I am when I’m not in the shed.

There, I think that does it. Hope you come back for an update.
fields.title: In the sticks (and on the farm)

fields.content:
New to Eastbourne Art are our Fragrant Heat Packs. The perfect stress remedy.

Available in our various fabrics, the heat pack is designed to shape to your body. Once heated they work at soothing aches and pains. Perfect for a sore neck or knee. Our heat packs are filled with barley infused with lavender flowers, which calm and relax you.

We added the fragrant heat packs to our range this year after making a few samples last year which were well received. My daughter is into therapeutic treatments and spent the last few months of her pregnancy last year with a heat pack draped over shoulders, lower back, tummy, head, tucked behind her whilst driving. The barley retains the heat really well.

The heat packs can be zapped in the microwave for 2 minutes, or heated in an oven. And they smell amazing.
fields.title: Therapeutic Fragrant Heat Packs

fields.title: Dates for your diary

fields.content:
Arcadian Artists started over 20 years ago when a small group of local artists opened their studios to their neighbours and the local community. Now held annually, the exhibition attracts a wide range of contributing artists that span the Hornsby and Baulkham Hills Shires.

We have been involved in the local event for the last three years, providing the farm as a venue, and showcasing our product range with other local artists.

For the 2010 weekend (13th-14th November), we are in the planning stages. I am once again putting together the brochure/location/venue map, which is distributed around Sydney and available on the exhibition weekend. (I will post a PDF for download once it is completed).

It's a great day out, and you have the opportunity to experience the exhibits amongst the eight studios (and get to take a peek at some gorgeous gardens).

I will confirm in the coming weeks which artists will be exhibiting on the farm.

Make it a date in your diary - Saturday 13th – Sunday 14th November 2010.

www.arcadianartists.com.au

fields.content:
Our new Christmas range has arrived (to our website).

Our Christmas range features seasonal designs on red, black, and charcoal fabric........I wanted to do something different this year, and the red & silver prints on the charcoal look gorgeous. And the silver tree print on both the aprons and t-towels looks very smart.

Rudolph with his bell & bow, an Eastboure Art favourite, feature amongst our new designs - Christmas trees, Christmas Angels, Reindeers, and a Christmas Wreath.

We have also our spot print aprons (red, taupe, black) with a festive gold star.

fields.title: About the Brand
fields.content:
Eastbourne Art had its beginnings in the family room with all the kids and the dog harmoniously enmeshed in a somewhat chaotic state. Known then as Eastbourne Barncraft the business was known for its aprons & t-towel range and we were invited to Art & Craft shows throughout the year. It wasn’t long before everything moved it into a beautiful purpose built stone barn, out of the house and in the bottom of the garden.


The first Trade Show was quite an experience. We had a small wall on the end of a friends stand and managed to come home with a number of orders. With only four products & three designs we had begun our wholesale business.
A move to the rural part of Northern Sydney opened up the space to grow a larger range of products including garden accessories, doorstops and the furnishing fabric range.


Creatively the ideas come with searching for fabrics, the colour palette and new and existing items to create and make into a complimentary range. The furnishing fabrics are vibrant, and of excellent quality. The main range including aprons and ironing board covers is made of canvas/drill which is hard wearing and guaranteed to give the user years of wear. Recently, in order to achieve a contemporary look, we have designed and had fabric hand printed by the metre as well as continuing to hand print the smaller designs on to the finished product items.

Eastbourne Art is a collection inspired by our rural surroundings & family life. There has always been a skew towards garden & the outdoors, as it’s where you'll find us when we are not in the shed.
